This code compiles ([rust playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=281358762a7b1e21825717972a7759cb)):

```rust
struct Foo<'a> {
    borrow: &'a mut usize
}

impl<'a> Foo<'a> {
    fn foo(&mut self) -> Foo<'_> {
        Foo { borrow: self.borrow }
    }
}

fn main() {
    let mut a = 0;
    let mut b = Foo { borrow: &mut a };
    b.foo();
}
```

This code does not ([rust playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=stable&mode=debug&edition=2018&gist=281358762a7b1e21825717972a7759cb)):

```rust

struct Foo<'a> {
    borrow: &'a mut usize
}

impl<'a> Foo<'a> {
    fn foo(&mut self) -> Foo<'_> {
        Self { borrow: self.borrow } /* Note changed Foo to Self here */
    }
}

fn main() {
    let mut a = 0;
    let mut b = Foo { borrow: &mut a };
    b.foo();
}
```
Instead giving the following error:

```
   Compiling playground v0.0.1 (/playground)
error[E0312]: lifetime of reference outlives lifetime of borrowed content...
 --> src/main.rs:8:24
  |
8 |         Self { borrow: self.borrow } /* Note changed Foo to Self here */
  |                        ^^^^^^^^^^^
  |
note: ...the reference is valid for the lifetime `'a` as defined on the impl at 6:6...
 --> src/main.rs:6:6
  |
6 | impl<'a> Foo<'a> {
  |      ^^
note: ...but the borrowed content is only valid for the anonymous lifetime #1 defined on the method body at 7:5
 --> src/main.rs:7:5
  |
7 | /     fn foo(&mut self) -> Foo<'_> {
8 | |         Self { borrow: self.borrow } /* Note changed Foo to Self here */
9 | |     }
  | |_____^

error: aborting due to previous error

For more information about this error, try `rustc --explain E0312`.
error: could not compile `playground`.

To learn more, run the command again with --verbose.
```
